ansion.<br><br>We have a wide level range in our guild how do people feel about this looting system? I'm just curious.<br><br><br>Trivial Loot Code and Luclin <br>- Aurum @ 6:55 PM PDT <br>The Trivial Loot subject was brought up by Brad McQuaid in his first visit to the Developer's Corner in a while:<br><br>Hello all,<br><br>I wanted to update you all on our current thoughts regarding the Trivial Loot Code as it relates to Shadows of Luclin zones.<br><br>As per my last couple of 'Ask Brads', we've made both an effort to explain what the Trivial Loot Code does and why we were considering it for all Luclin zones. I'd also mentioned, however, that if most players appeared to be against its inclusion we'd not use it.<br><br>After talking with players, reading emails and feedback, and then very recently running a poll, it is indeed apparent that the majority of our playerbase does not feel that the Loot Code's advantages outweigh its restrictions.<br><br>In fact, after polling over 200,000 players, most want the looting system left alone, almost as many want us to explore a different solution for bottom feeding and rampant farming, and a minority were in favor of the Trivial Loot Code as it exists today in the Warrens and Stonebrunt Mountains (the remainder either didn't have an opinion or were unfamiliar with TLC).<br><br>Well, so be it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>We will head back to our drawing boards and keep brainstorming on this issue, but at this current time we do NOT intend on implementing TLC for the zones in our upcoming expansion, the Shadows of Luclin.<br><br>I do want to thank everyone for all the feedback and discussion regarding this issue -- there was a lot of debate surrounding this issue, and we've done our best to pay attention. <br><br>-Brad McQuaid<br>Chief Creative Officer &amp; Vice President<br>Sony Online Entertainment/Verant Interactive<br> <p>Stupie Silverthorn.53 season Ranger...and thats an "E" at the end, not a "D".........</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/uriphen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Riphen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/21/01 11:20:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No TLC for Luclin?</span><hr size=1> Thank Jebus.<br><br>Riphen<br>STFD! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/ulasalle77.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lasalle77</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/22/01 5:05:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No TLC for Luclin?</span><hr size=1> <br>See what I mean?  Verant is for us, folks.  Whether they're only doing it to make more money for themselves or not-- both Verant and the majority of players polled are going to be getting their way.  <br><br>I still think Verant cares about us, despite the money-- think about it.  How many people here can honestly say that they wouldn't care to see/buy Luclin if a trivial loot code was active in all of its' zones?  The game is about fun, first and foremost-- loot is only one aspect of the fun I have while playing.  Whether they implemented a TLC for Luclin or not.. I'm still going to buy it.  The world/universe of Norrath is expanding so quickly!  Why wouldn't you want to share in this new experience?  So the bottom line, is that I don't feel the way some do-- I don't think Verant is always trying to screw us over.  Of course, being a level 40, perhaps I haven't felt the problems associated with being a very high level character and not being able to complete a quest due to the TLC.  Just my 2cp.  <br><br>Lasalle   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=151.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm1.showNextMessage?topicID=151.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm1.emailToFriend?topicID=151.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm1.threadControl?topicID=151.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=151.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=151.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub88.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><se